    public class Planning
extends java.lang.Object

      • computeRoute

        public void computeRoute(javafx.event.EventHandler<javafx.concurrent.WorkerStateEvent> handler)
        Starts the route computing in a new thread. Update the deliveries time as well. The handler will be notified when the route computing will be done. An ArithmeticException can be thrown throught the thread, if any route can't be found.
        Parameters:
        handler - The event handler to notify and the route computing is finished.

      • computeRoute

        Adds a delivery to the planning, after another delivery. Notifies the planning and route subscribers when it's done.

        node - The node where we want to add a delivery
        nodePreviousDelivery - The node where is the delivery to do before the new one we want to add.
        timeSlot - The time slot in which we want the new delivery to be.
        Returns:
